The paper discusses a novel RDF indexing technique for efficient SPARQL resolution in compressed space, which is a topic related to database systems (cs.DB). The technique also involves optimization of join algorithms, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of compact indexes and leverages specific features of the data model, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
